rooms.name: Royal Treasury
rooms.description: You step into the Royal Treasury and the vaulted chamber swallows sound, your footsteps answering with a distant, hollow thud against cold flagged stone. Sparse pedestals, a lone iron-bound chest, and a few ornate caskets punctuate the vastness, their edges catching the weak light and the occasional glint of coin like cold embers. The air tastes of metal and old seals, and every shadow seems to guard a quiet accounting of riches no one has touched for years.

rooms.name: Empty Guard Post
rooms.description: You slip into the Empty Guard Post, a modest chamber where a narrow cot, a splintered stool and a scarred table hold only a stub of candle and a dented iron cup. A cold draft sighs through the arrow-slit, lifting the scent of wet wool and old sweat, and every scuff and nail-hole waits like a quiet accusation for footsteps that never returned.
